t360.text: What makes someone assume that that the sum of one human’s vices makes them any less worthy of engagement? To assume the stance that the best life is a life without vices is IMO ignorant AF. It is impossible to gauge the burdens others carry, let alone exist without a vice.

t361.text: What’s the point of a life in general? It is to be lived IMO. What makes a life lived with some vices, any less worth living? I’ve lived the best I can thus far and I will continue to do so. I’ve done my level best wherever I can. I stand by & strive for this every day I wake up.

t362.text: Everything must end, so why the drama surrounding the matter? When it comes time to ‘check out’ I intend to make no fuss and peace out in style. But then again, I recognise that that statement in itself is a form of ego. How can I possibly fathom how I will feel when it’s my time

t363.text: Was I triggered? Yes I was, but I remained respectful in my tone and delivery. Don’t tell me what the feck to do with my life. We all do the best we can, with what we have, while carrying the crosses we bear. But that got me thinking how much people are afraid of death.
